## 9. Visual Design Standards

Consistency is the default. A screen should use different styling only for a clear functional reason.

### Core palette

| Purpose | Color |
|---|---|
| Main background | `#0f1722` or `#0b1220` |
| Panel background | `#1e293b` |
| Secondary dark panel | `#111827` |
| Primary text | `#ffffff` |
| Secondary text | `#9ca3af` |
| Gold accent | `#f5c451` |
| Blue action accent | `#2563eb` |
| Red danger accent | `#7f1d1d` |

### Interface character

Prefer:

- Dark blue backgrounds.
- Slate panels.
- Gold headings and identity accents.
- Blue normal-action buttons.
- Red only for destructive or dangerous actions.
- Rounded cards.
- Clear spacing.
- High readability.
- Restrained medieval-fantasy styling.

Avoid:

- Inconsistent palettes between screens.
- Decorative effects that reduce readability.
- Overly ornate fantasy borders.
- Animation added only for spectacle.
- Excessively long pages where existing information can be reorganized.

### Responsive layout

- Kingdom selection should normally remain two columns, including on standard phones.
- It may fall back to one column only at unusually narrow widths.
- Text must not overlap, clip, or force horizontal scrolling.
- Future additions to Stats must fit within the existing page footprint unless a deliberate redesign is approved.

